      • userTest

        public void userTest()
              throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests whether a User object was successfully created by checking if their name matches the name provided.

      • groupTest

        public void groupTest()
               throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests whether a Group object was successfully created by checking if the group size is equal to 1 after creation. Size 1 is obtained from the creator being the only member of that group.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - on unsuccessful Group object creation.

      • addUserToGroupTest

        public void addUserToGroupTest()
                        throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests whether adding a user to a group was successful by checking if the group size is equal to 2 after adding a group member. Size 2 is obtained from the creator and the added user being the only members of that group.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - on unsuccessful user add to group.

      • removeUserToGroupTest

        public void removeUserToGroupTest()
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests whether removing a user from a group was successful by checking if the group size is equal to 1 after removing a group member. The group size is 2 before user removal, and so should be 1 after removing the user.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - on unsuccessful user remove from group.

      • freestateUserTest

        public void freestateUserTest()
                       throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests that a newly created user is in the free agent state by default.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - on the new user not being in the free agent state.

      • userCreatesGroupTest

        public void userCreatesGroupTest()
                          throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests that a user who creates a group is in the creator state.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - on the user not being in the creator state after making a group.

      • memberTest

        public void memberTest()
                throws java.lang.Exception
        Tests that a user who joins a group is in the member state.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - on the user not being in the member state after joining a group.
